Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to
425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Dice @sweet potato{2}%unit into ½-inch pieces. Trim,
peel, and halve @carrot{3%oz}; cut into pieces about the size of the green beans.
Zest and quarter @lemon{1}%unit.

Place sweet potatoes in a medium #pot with enough salted water to cover to by 2
inches. Boil until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Drain and return sweet potatoes to pot.
Mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth, then stir in @sour cream{4%tbsp} and season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, pat @chicken breasts{12%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with
@salt{}, @pepper{}, and half the @sweet and smoky BBQ seasoning{1%tbsp} (use all for
4 servings). Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{5%tsp} in a #medium pan{} over
medium-high heat. Add chicken; sear until golden brown but not yet cooked through,
~{2-4%minutes} per side (it'll finish cooking in the oven). Turn off heat; transfer
chicken to one side of a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}. Wipe out pan.

On opposite side of baking sheet from chicken, toss @green beans{6%oz} and carrot
with a large drizzle of oil, salt, and pepper. (For 4 servings, add veggies to a
second baking sheet; roast veggies on top rack and chicken on middle rack.) Roast
on top rack until chicken is cooked through and veggies are tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.
Remove from oven; let chicken rest.

Once chicken has roasted 10 minutes, heat pan used for chicken over medium-high heat.
Add ¼ cup water (⅓ cup for 4 servings), @chicken stock concentrate{1%unit}, and
@honey{4%tsp}. Bring to a simmer and cook until slightly thickened, ~{2-4%minutes}.
Reduce heat to low and stir in @butter{2%tbsp} (3 TBSP for 4) until melted. Season with
salt and pepper.

Toss green beans and carrot with lemon zest and juice to taste. Divide between plates
with sweet potatoes. Top sweet potatoes with chicken and drizzle with sauce. Sprinkle
with @chili flakes{1%tsp} to taste. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Our philosophy? BBQ chicken is a summer staple that shouldn't be limited to those who
> have a grill or know how to grill. All you need is a good sear and a quick trip in
> the oven to achieve perfectly juicy, smoky-sweet results! This recipe is so simple
> and delicious, especially when mashed sweet potatoes and lemony roasted veggies are
> involved. Goodbye, grill!